author: Jack Roskopp
title: Apparently snowplows in Michigan have names, and they‚Äôre all hilarious
text: If you live in a part of the country where you experience all four seasons, then you‚Äôre pretty used to snowplows cleaning the streets of your town, whenever Mother Nature decides to dump inches of snow on the ground. But did you know that these snowplows actually have names -- and most of them are beyond hilarious? [Twitter user Alec Stapp tweeted](https://twitter.com/AlecStapp/status/1480900917734129666) a list of all the snowplows in Michigan that are named, from the Michigan Department of Transportation. We looked into it too, [and it turns out, the department really does have a list](https://www.michigan.gov/mdot/0,4616,7-151-9615-575096--,00.html) of snowplow names sorted by region, and they‚Äôre really funny. This list of Michigan Department of Transportation snowplow names will melt your icy heart‚Äî Alec Stapp (@AlecStapp) [pic.twitter.com/RmV4PU8mIS] [January 11, 2022] And I don‚Äôt mean a light giggle kind of funny -- I‚Äôm talking about laugh out loud funny. The level of pun work with words like ‚Äúsnow,‚Äù ‚Äúsalt,‚Äù and ‚Äúplow‚Äù is truly next level. Just reading the list, I could sense my seasonal depression melting away. I might actually make it through this wave of omicron, thanks to this list. So without further ado, let‚Äôs go through some of my favorite snowplow names (in no particular order), and have a good laugh, shall we? Big Bertha Look, you just want to meet the person who drives a snowplow named Big Bertha. You don‚Äôt mess with them. Saltosaurus Rex Our first pun! There is also a Plowasaurus Rex on the mega list of names, but we‚Äôve got to give it to Saltosaurus Rex. No snow is safe when this plow is around. Snowdown Please, I‚Äôm Plowing It‚Äôs a pun, but it‚Äôs also not a name pun, so this makes it even better. And the driver of this plow is correct: You should slow down while they‚Äôre plowing! Baby Snowda This is the first (of many) ‚ÄúStar Wars‚Äù puns, which has me thinking that people who drive snowplows are just giant nerds? We say that with love! Fast and Flurryous OK, I adore this one. Not only is it a great pun, but they used the word ‚Äúflurry‚Äù when most of the puns we see involve ‚Äúplow‚Äù or ‚Äúsalt.‚Äù Bravo! Sleetwood Mac OMG, the joy this name brought me when I first saw it. Again, ‚Äúsleet‚Äù is a word we don‚Äôt see used for puns on this list, so hats off for the creativity. And who doesn‚Äôt love Fleetwood Mac? Bringin‚Äô Pavement Back Besides this being a play on ‚ÄúSexyBack‚Äù by Justin Timberlake, this is literally what a snowplow does. This name is entertaining and informative. Alice Scooper This is an A+ pun and this person also gets bonus point because Alice Cooper is from Michigan. It‚Äôs a win-win. Han Snow-Lo This continues our trend of many ‚ÄúStar Wars‚Äù puns. Like I said, I think these snowplow drivers are just huge nerds, and I am here for it. Snowbegone Kenobi OK, but this one is the best of the ‚ÄúStar Wars‚Äù names. I applaud you. Orange Yooper Storm Trooper Not really a pun, but I do appreciate a good rhyme! Still Shorts Weather We all know that guy who wears shorts in the middle of winter on the one day when the sun‚Äôs out and the temp is just about 40 degrees. This snowplow is an ode to that dude. Betty Whiteout Too soon? Nah, I think it‚Äôs a loving tribute. Live on, Betty! Ctrl Salt Delete I have no words. This is genius. Plowthagorean Theorem OK, you can all go home now. This one wins. Also, more nerds driving snowplows. Salt Whitman The inner English major in me is smiling so hard at this name. My heart burst with the intensity of 1,000 suns. Edgar Allan Snow Again, God bless the people who come up with these names. Melton John I‚Äôm done. Snowprah Winfrey THIS ONE WINS, GOOD-BYE.

author: brennon
title: Snap Up The New US Rangers Plastic Set For Warlord‚Äôs Bolt Action
text:
Warlord Games are taking pre-orders right now for a new 28mm plastic set for your games of Bolt Action . You can snap up the US Rangers for your World War II wargames where you're prepping to dive into the Allied pushback against the Axis.
US Rangers Box // Bolt Action Shop Bolt Action @ Store.OnTableTop As Warlord has noted on their webstore. The Rangers were vital in the Allied invasion of French North Africa called Operation Torch. They also then took place in the landings in Sicily in 1943 and in the invasion of mainland Italy. You would have also found them on the beaches of Normandy during Operation Overlord where they scaled Pointe du Hoc to take out German gun emplacements. More of them were also on Omaha Beach battling out of the surf in order to push back the Germans and secure those landing grounds.
US Rangers Miniatures // Bolt Action With that in mind, you can see why the Rangers are such an iconic force for use in World War II and why it's great to have a nice new plastic set. You can "lead the way" with this big boxed set, perhaps in the new edition of Bolt Action.
The set comes with enough plastic bits to make thirty US Rangers with a host of different weapon options and with enough to make command miniatures too. To give you an idea of the components on the sprue, they have "M1 Garand rifle, M1 carbine, Thompson SMG, M1 Bazooka, BAR, Bangalore torpedoes, Satchel charges, hand grenades, Browning pistol, Springfield M1903A4 sniper rifle, pick/mattocks, axes & wire cutters".
There are also some additional heads based on Saving Private Ryan which is a fun touch. It's good to have these ways to bring in people who have experienced the "Hollywood" take on World War II.
USMC Miniatures For The Pacific If you'd like to enhance your armies for battling in the Pacific, you can also get your hands on two sets for the USMC. Leading the way is the War Dog Team .
USMC War Dog Teams// Bolt Action This set of two metal handlers and their metal dogs are good for introducing the dog platoons of 1943. Most of the dogs used were German Shepherds but there were also Doberman Pinschers. They were both scout dogs and messenger dogs that could help their handlers keep an eye out for ambushes, hidden snipers and more. They were incredibly good at that job and even as messengers they would rush through hails of bullets to find their target. Many were wounded in the course of duty and were as embattled as their human companions!
You can also get your hands on a USMC Forward Observer Team .
USMC Forward Observer Team // Bolt Action This set comes in metal as well as features three figures. You have a team watching from behind enemy lines getting ready to call in airstrikes and artillery shells on enemy positions. One of them is checking their map whilst another is on the blower. The third character is watching out for enemies with his Thompson.
Are you going to be picking up some of these new Bolt Action miniatures?

author: @AKNewsNow
title: Search efforts suspended for missing Eagle River women who fell under the ice
text: Family mourning, grateful for community support after missing Eagle River woman fell under the ice EAGLE RIVER, Alaska (KTUU) - The family of an Eagle River nurse, wife and mom who went missing in icy waters over the Christmas weekend trying to save her dog, are in shock and say the kindness from the community is beyond words. After four days of searching, Alaska Wildlife Troopers have [suspended the active search efforts](https://dailydispatch.dps.alaska.gov/Home/DisplayIncident?incidentNumber=AK23131423) for Amanda Richmond Rogers, who went missing last Saturday near North Fork Eagle River Trail. On Thursday night, Jennifer Richmond, the sister of Amanda Richmond Rogers, released the following statement: ‚ÄúThe Alaska State Troopers informed our family on Dec 27 that the active search for my sister, Amanda Richmond Rogers, has been suspended. In our families‚Äô grief, we want to extend our heartfelt gratitude to the [Alaska Dive Search Rescue and Recovery Team](https://sites.google.com/inetwiz.com/akdiverescue/memorial-fund?authuser=0), a non-profit organization of volunteers who spent the past few days, literally on their hands and knees when not actually diving in the river where Mandy disappeared, shepherding a sonar device through the icy waters. As many who knew Mandy know, she loved all animals, but especially her dogs. Indeed, it was in a rescue attempt for her dog Groot that she dove into the mostly frozen river. She would‚Äôve made this choice for her dogs and family again, without a second thought. We know that those at the [Alaska Solstice Search Dogs](https://linkprotect.cudasvc.com/url?a=https%3a%2f%2fwww.alaskasolsticesearchdogs.com%2f&c=E,1,RjFHc8yQQ-D4LTqejQ-ANkou2Z3Lbx71Dt4JtS3hQGS6ILZu9Vp90tTo3qDZy9mgSZ1iwL9q14qYT7gl7-cD0pqWV6SKl8XjvqCLsBxzW4s,&typo=1), who were also involved in her search, committed their time and energy with the same dedication Mandy had for her own family, both dog and human (her four sons were her life). It is to these two organizations that we have created a Memorial Fund to honor both her name and their work. We have created a [Facebook page](https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=61554977644365) for those who want more information on donations, our continued search, our upcoming celebration of life and to share stories of the beautiful life of an infinitely kind and generous soul. As we hold each other close, we try to find comfort in knowing that Mandy, who loved mermaids, is now swimming free as our arctic angel who continues to bless all those lucky enough to have brushed against her enormous heart.‚Äù Troopers say Richmond Rogers disappeared [under the frozen open water](https://www.alaskasnewssource.com/2023/12/24/search-rescue-woman-falls-through-ice-eagle-river/) of the North Fork of Eagle River while trying to rescue her dog that had fallen into the water. ‚ÄúWe have run out of areas of interest that are accessible to search with the ice and the conditions in the area,‚Äù Alaska State Troopers spokesperson Austin McDaniel said. ‚ÄúThis certainly was not the result we were looking for and we‚Äôre definitely open to looking for new information, new evidence that might help us narrow down that search area.‚Äù Drones, helicopters, divers, K9 teams, sonar and remotely operated vehicles (ROV) were all employed, according to AST. Besides the troopers, the Anchorage Police Department, Anchorage Fire Department and the Alaska Dive Search, Rescue and Recovery Team also contributed to the search. ‚ÄúAnytime you‚Äôre searching under the ice for somebody, it is not an easy area to search in,‚Äù McDaniel said. ‚ÄúYou have varying thicknesses of ice, it‚Äôs a winding river, varying depths of that river, different channels within the river.‚Äù The dive team encountered some equipment issues during the search, according to McDaniel, but he added that weather was not a major impediment to the search. ‚ÄúI don‚Äôt think the outside weather conditions are restricting us. It‚Äôs just the thicknesses of the ice, the depths of the water really make it a more challenging environment to search in,‚Äù he said. APD lists Richmond Rogers as a missing person. author: Record staff
title: Kingdom Ministries invites public to Easter dinner in Troy
text:
TROY, N.Y. ‚Äî Kingdom Ministries invites one and all to their 14th annual free community Easter dinner this Sunday.
The meal will be offered at 1:30 pm, at Christ Church on 35 State Street. This year it is being served as an Italian family-style meal, prepared by people Kingdom Ministries president Billy Carter describes as ‚Äúthe best cooks in the Capital District.‚Äù Everyone is welcome to attend.
Desserts will be provided by Bella Napoli, thanks to generous support from Dominic Mainella.
The meal is being prepared by Peter Enzien, Joe Anne Enzien, Antoinette Schnellbacher, Susan France, Luanne Vazzana, Pasqua Leno, Michael Yamin, and Antoinette Yamin.
‚ÄúThe holiday dinners were started to honor Jesus Christ and bring people into a relationship with him through our service and the fact that there was no place to go for community in Troy and food if you were lonely,‚Äù Carter said. ‚ÄúWe wanted there to be a place for happiness and the love of God to shine through, and God answered my prayer.‚Äù
In addition to free food for 200 people, Kingdom Ministries will also have gently used clothes and housewares available to anyone that needs them.
‚ÄúWe are so grateful to our donors, Troy Savings Bank Music Hall, Nite Owl News, Louis Coplin, Lee Groff, Haven Brown, Bishop William Love, Troy Firefighters Union, Peg Walsh, Rodney and Jolene Wiltshire, and Victorious Life Church,‚Äù Carter said. ‚ÄúI also want to give thanks to my wonderful beautiful wife Lucille, who always always gathers donations and helps in so many ways.‚Äù
For more information, contact Billy Carter at 518-935-7377.
